recalls.Component: SERVICE BRAKES, HYDRAULIC:ANTILOCK/TRACTION CONTROL/ELECTRONIC LIMITED SLIP:CONTROL UNIT/MODULE
recalls.Summary: Honda (America Honda Motor Co.) is recalling certain 2023 Civic, Acura RDX, Acura Integra, and 2022 Honda Accord vehicles.  A ball valve in the vehicle stability assist (VSA) modulator may leak brake fluid, which can result in unintended vehicle movement when the brake hold feature is engaged or an unexpected increase in brake pedal travel.
recalls.Consequence: Unintended vehicle movement or an unexpected increase in brake pedal travel can increase the risk of a crash or injury.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will replace the VSA modulator, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed July 24, 2023.  Owners may contact Honda customer service at 1-888-234-2138.  Honda's numbers for this recall are OEJ, XEK, AEY, XEX and OEW.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Honda (American Honda Motor Co.) is recalling certain 2022-2024 Civic 4-door and Civic 5-door vehicles that received a replacement power steering rack as part of a service repair.  The steering rack may have been incorrectly assembled, which can allow the tire to chafe against the lower suspension or tie rod end, possibly resulting in tire damage.
recalls.Consequence: A damaged tire can fail and increase the risk of a crash or injury.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will inspect and replace the electric power steering rack, as necessary, free of charge.  Owner letters were mailed January 16, 2024.  Owners may contact Honda customer service at 1-888-234-2138.  Honda's number for this recall is YFW.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Honda (American Honda Motor Co.) is recalling certain 2023-2025 Acura Integra, Civic Type R, CR-V Hybrid, CR-V, HR-V, 2022-2025 Civic, Civic Hatchback, 2024-2025 Acura Integra Type S, 2025 CR-V Fuel Cell EV, Civic Hybrid, and Civic Hatchback Hybrid vehicles.  The steering gearbox assembly may have been manufactured incorrectly, which can cause excessive internal friction and lead to difficulty steering the vehicle.
recalls.Consequence: Difficulty steering can increase the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will replace the worm gear spring and redistribute or add grease as necessary, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed November 18, 2024.  Owners may contact Honda Customer Service at 1-888-234-2138.   Honda's numbers for this recall are SJS, MJU, QJT and VJV.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153) or go to nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Honda (American Honda Motor Co.) is recalling certain 2023-2024 Honda Accord, Accord Hybrid, Civic Sedan, Civic Hatchback, Pilot, and 2024 HR-V, Acura Integra and Acura Integra Type S vehicles.  The driver's seat cushion frame may not have been tightened properly, which can result in an unsecured seat.  As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard number 207, "Seating Systems."
recalls.Consequence: An unsecured driver's seat may not adequately restrain the driver during a crash, increasing the risk of injury.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will replace the driver's seat cushion frame, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed January 6, 2025.  Owners may contact Honda customer service at 1-888-234-2138.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153) or go to nhtsa.gov.

issues.title: Intermittent Engine Stalling at Idle
issues.description: Multiple owners report engine stalling unexpectedly while idling, particularly when coming to a stop or during warm-up. The issue appears to be related to the electronic throttle body or fuel delivery system.
issues.fix_description: Throttle body cleaning, software update, or throttle body replacement
issues.prevention: Regular maintenance, avoid extended idle periods, use quality fuel

issues.title: Turbo Wastegate Actuator Failure
issues.description: Early failure of the turbocharger wastegate actuator leading to reduced boost pressure and power loss. Some units failing within the first year of ownership.
issues.fix_description: Wastegate actuator replacement, potentially full turbocharger replacement
issues.prevention: Proper warm-up procedures, quality oil changes, avoid aggressive driving when cold

issues.title: Air Conditioning Compressor Clutch Failure
issues.description: A/C compressor clutch failing prematurely, resulting in no air conditioning function. Issue reported by multiple owners during first year of ownership.
issues.fix_description: A/C compressor clutch replacement or full compressor replacement
issues.prevention: Regular A/C system maintenance, avoid excessive idle with A/C on

issues.title: Brake Pedal Feel Issues
issues.description: Owners report inconsistent brake pedal feel, including soft or spongy brakes despite proper bleeding. Some cases require multiple brake fluid flushes or master cylinder service.
issues.fix_description: Brake fluid flush, brake system bleeding, potential master cylinder service
issues.prevention: Regular brake fluid changes, proper bedding of brake pads

issues.title: Fuel Injector Carbon Buildup
issues.description: Direct injection engines prone to carbon buildup on intake valves and fuel injectors, causing rough idle and reduced performance. Issue typically emerges after 15,000-25,000 miles.
issues.fix_description: Intake valve and injector cleaning service, fuel system cleaning
issues.prevention: Use top-tier gasoline, periodic fuel system cleaning, avoid short trips

issues.title: Transmission Rev Hang
issues.description: Manual transmission exhibits excessive rev hang between gear changes, particularly noticeable during spirited driving. While not damaging, it affects driving experience and shift timing.
issues.fix_description: ECU software update, aftermarket tune, or drive-by-wire recalibration
issues.prevention: No prevention available, characteristic of emissions tuning

issues.title: Rear Spoiler Wind Noise
issues.description: Excessive wind noise generated by the large rear spoiler at highway speeds. Some owners report whistling or buffeting sounds that become intrusive during long drives.
issues.fix_description: Spoiler adjustment, adding wind deflectors, or aftermarket spoiler modifications

issues.title: Paint Quality Issues
issues.description: Reports of soft paint that chips and scratches easily, particularly on the front bumper and hood. Some owners note paint defects from factory including orange peel and color matching issues.
issues.fix_description: Paint correction, touch-up, or panel repainting
issues.prevention: Paint protection film, careful washing techniques, covered parking

issues.title: Clutch Pedal Spring Noise
issues.description: Annoying squeaking or creaking noise from clutch pedal spring mechanism during engagement and disengagement. Does not affect function but creates NVH issues.
issues.fix_description: Lubrication of pedal mechanism, spring replacement, or bushing service

issues.title: Infotainment System Freezing
issues.description: Honda infotainment system experiencing random freezes and crashes, requiring system restart. Some units fail to respond to touch inputs or display glitched graphics.
issues.fix_description: Software update, system reset, or infotainment unit replacement
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme temperatures, regular software updates when available

editorial.hero_blurb: The FL5 Civic Type R represents Honda's most refined hot hatch yet, delivering 315 turbocharged horses through a sublime six-speed manual. This isn't just fast—it's surgically precise, blending everyday usability with track-day capability in a way that makes every commute feel like a canyon run.
editorial.essence: The FL5 Type R is Honda's masterclass in chassis tuning and turbo engineering, offering genuine supercar-slaying performance wrapped in practical hatchback packaging. It's a car that rewards skill while remaining approachable enough for daily duty, representing the pinnacle of front-wheel-drive dynamics.
editorial.heritage: Born from Honda's racing DNA, the Type R badge first appeared in 1992 with the NSX-R. The Civic Type R lineage began in 1997, evolving through naturally aspirated screaming engines to this turbocharged FL5 generation that maintains the hardcore philosophy while embracing modern forced induction.
editorial.design_philosophy: Honda's engineers prioritized function over flash, creating aggressive aerodynamics that actually work while maintaining the Type R's unmistakable visual drama. Every vent, wing, and diffuser serves a purpose, channeling air for cooling or downforce while announcing the car's serious intentions.
editorial.motorsport_history: The Type R legacy is built on circuit success, from BTCC championships to Time Attack records. The FL5 carries this torch with Nürburgring-honed suspension geometry and aero packages developed through countless track hours, proving its mettle at circuits worldwide.
editorial.engine_character: The K20C1 turbo four delivers relentless, linear power with minimal lag, building boost aggressively from 2,500 rpm to a screaming 7,000 rpm redline. It's brutally efficient yet emotionally engaging, combining modern turbo torque with Honda's legendary high-rev enthusiasm.
editorial.transmission_feel: The six-speed manual is a tactile masterpiece—short, precise throws with perfectly weighted action and a rev-matching system that makes heel-toe downshifts effortless. Each gear change feels mechanical and direct, connecting driver to drivetrain with surgical precision.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: The FL5's chassis is a revelation, managing 315hp through the front wheels with minimal torque steer while maintaining composure through the most demanding corners. Adaptive dampers and a sophisticated limited-slip differential create a platform that's both forgiving and wickedly fast.
editorial.steering_feel: Electrically assisted but mechanically connected, the steering offers genuine feedback and precise weighting that builds naturally with cornering forces. It's communicative enough to place the car exactly where you want it while remaining manageable in traffic.
editorial.brake_confidence: Brembo four-piston calipers deliver fade-resistant stopping power with a firm, progressive pedal feel that inspires confidence on track. The system balances initial bite with modulation, allowing precise trail-braking while hauling down from triple-digit speeds repeatedly.
editorial.sound_signature: The FL5 produces a sophisticated growl—deep turbo whooshes on acceleration building to a metallic wail at redline, punctuated by aggressive pops and crackles on overrun. It's loud enough to thrill enthusiasts while remaining civilized for daily use.
editorial.ideal_owner: Driving purists who demand both track capability and daily usability will find their perfect match. This car suits experienced enthusiasts who appreciate mechanical precision and can exploit the FL5's considerable performance envelope.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Buyers seeking luxury appointments, automatic transmissions, or subtle styling should look elsewhere. Those uncomfortable with firm suspension and aggressive driving dynamics will find the Type R too uncompromising for their tastes.
editorial.buyers_summary: The FL5 represents the sweet spot of modern hot hatches—serious performance without supercar compromises. Find a well-maintained example and prepare for a driving experience that redefines what front-wheel drive can accomplish.

expertReviews.title: Civic Type R FL5 - 1 Year Ownership Review
pros: Spoon lowering springs improve ride comfort over stock
PPF protection effective against rock chips after 6,000 miles
315 horsepower K20C1 engine provides adequate street performance
MaxSpider 3D floor mats fit perfectly and are durable
OEM illuminated door sill plates add nice aesthetic touch
Found spare tire solution for $45 vs $300+ OEM option
cons: Key fob system makes car easier to steal than traditional key
Coolant reservoir known to fail along seam, expensive to replace ($300-500)
Plastic valve cover instead of aluminum like older K-series
Washer bottle hose routing looks like an afterthought
No spare tire included from factory
Expensive protection package cost nearly $4,000
expertReviews.verdict: After one year and 6,000 miles, the FL5 Type R proves to be a capable daily driver with successful modifications including Spoon springs, PPF protection, and wheel spacers. While the owner appreciates the performance and has invested heavily in protection and upgrades, there are concerns about build quality details like the plastic coolant reservoir and valve cover compared to previous generations.

expertReviews.title: Is It Really Worth £50000? | Honda Civic Type-R Review | FL5
pros: Best looking Civic Type R ever made - gorgeous design
Fastest front-wheel drive car to lap the Nürburgring
Excellent 6-speed manual gearbox - tight, precise, lovely feel
Very capable handling with sharp front end and LSD
Premium interior materials with Alcantara seats and steering wheel
Can be daily driven comfortably - refined and compliant
Functional aerodynamics including bonnet vent and rear spoiler
Strong engine performance with linear power delivery and VTEC
Adaptive dampers and wider track for improved cornering
cons: £50,000 price tag - £10,000 increase over inflation-adjusted FK8 price
No automatic gearbox option limits sales potential
Suspension too firm in +R mode for UK roads
Rev limiter at 3,500 RPM when stationary
Boot capacity reduced by 10 liters compared to FK8
30kg heavier than predecessor
Modern car annoyances - multiple submenus to disable driver aids
expertReviews.verdict: The FL5 Civic Type R is a mature evolution that delivers the best front-wheel drive hot hatch experience currently available. Despite the steep £50,000 price tag, it justifies the cost with exceptional build quality, premium materials, and outstanding driving dynamics. The reviewer was genuinely impressed and considered purchasing one himself, praising its ability to be both a capable track weapon and comfortable daily driver.

expertReviews.title: 2024 Honda Civic Type R FL5 REVIEW // it doesn't get any " by Paragon Cars London
pros: 330 horsepower and 420 Nm torque with phenomenal corner performance
Unique dual axis McPherson strut suspension and sublime steering feel
Excellent manual gearbox with auto rev-match and short throw
Weighs only 1.4 tons with track-ready capability
Best-in-class front-wheel drive handling and connection to road
cons: Very loud inside at over 70 decibels on motorway
Poor comfort even in comfort mode compared to rivals
Intrusive safety systems and annoying speed warning menus
Not ideal for daily driving on regular roads
Lacks sound deadening and refinement
expertReviews.verdict: The Honda Civic Type R FL5 is described as the 'GT3 of front-wheel drive hothatches' with unmatched engineering and handling capabilities. While it excels on twisty roads and tracks with phenomenal performance (4.36s 30-70mph), it's compromised for daily use due to noise and comfort issues. Despite these drawbacks, it's considered well worth the premium price for driving enthusiasts seeking the ultimate FWD experience.

expertReviews.title: 2024 Honda Civic Type R Review - Ultimate Dual Duty FL5
pros: Excellent dual duty capability
Outstanding brake feel with Brembo Pista upgrade
Sharp and responsive handling
Maintains daily drivability despite modifications
Quick acceleration with 330 wheel horsepower
Excellent grip and power delivery for FWD
cons: Noticeable torque steer with modifications
Aftermarket shifter compromises daily usability
Loud squeaky brakes
Limited downforce for track use
expertReviews.verdict: This modified Civic Type R FL5 represents the quintessential SoCal dual duty build. With careful modifications including Nitron R3 coilovers, Brembo Pista brakes, and a conservative tune producing 330whp, it maintains excellent daily drivability while being track-capable. The car achieved a 1:54 lap time at Buttonwillow and demonstrates the platform's inherent strengths with enhanced performance that doesn't compromise its versatile nature.

expertReviews.title: 2024 Honda Civic Type R Review - Heaviest and Quietest ...
pros: Excellent handling and grip with front LSD
Best OEM shifter on sale today
High chassis rigidity
Comfortable and aggressive seats
10 dB noise reduction with sound deadening
Still capable on canyon roads despite added weight
cons: Significant road and tire noise in stock form
Stiff suspension even in comfort mode on bumpy roads
Added 165 lbs reduces performance potential

expertReviews.verdict: This extensively sound-deadened FL5 Type R proves that 165 lbs of Amazon sound deadening materials can transform the car's refinement without significantly impacting handling dynamics. The 10 dB noise reduction makes it much more livable for daily driving and long distances, though purists may question adding weight to a performance-focused car. For drivers with noise sensitivity, the trade-off appears worthwhile.

expertReviews.title: Honda Civic Type R Review - Ultimate FWD Racer for the ...
pros: Exceptional grip and handling for front-wheel drive
Most comfortable sport seats reviewer has experienced
Practical daily driver that transforms into track weapon
Excellent manual gearbox with rev matching
Strong Brembo brakes
Lighter weight than previous generation (1540kg)
Keyless entry system is very convenient
Honda LogR system for track data monitoring
cons: Very expensive at 629,900 Swedish crowns (~$58,000)
Harsh ride quality over bumps
Gear shifter can be difficult when engaging reverse
Some cheap plastic interior materials
Horn sounds too light/tinny for the car's character
Infotainment screen could be angled better toward driver
expertReviews.verdict: The FL5 Honda Civic Type R is the ultimate front-wheel drive performance car, offering incredible grip, responsive handling, and surprising daily usability. Despite the high price, it delivers a pure driving experience that can challenge much more expensive sports cars on twisty roads. The reviewer lived with it for 3+ weeks and found it genuinely practical while being a track-focused beast when needed. A potential future collector's car representing the pinnacle of hardcore FWD performance.
